Two suspects aged 27 and 41 were arrested on Sunday night for malicious damage to property. These suspects were part of a group of people that damaged and burned properties including cars in the Gilead area outside Mokopane. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said is alleged that a group of people armed with varieties of dangerous weapons, arrived at Harmony village, attacked a family and burnt a cattle kraal and stole some of the cattle. He said the group proceeded to another house in the same area, where they also attacked another family and burnt their car, damaged other properties before they fled the scene. “The initial investigations and manhunt ensued which led to the arrest of the two suspects.” Ngoepe said the motive behind these incidents is not clear at this stage, but the ongoing Police investigations will tell. The arrested suspects will soon appear before Gilead Periodical Court soon. The Provincial Commissioner of the South African Police Service in Limpopo Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba condemned the reckless act by members of the community in this area. 